		<div id="comment_body_64979837">I think when you consider that there are currently over 6000 Starlink satellites, with plans to deploy over 12,000 and a possible later extension to 34,000 satellites, and communications can take multiple routes through the network, then your total network bandwidth isn't limited to the bandwidth of one satellite.  You only have to be able to multiplex over 100 of those thousands of satellites to reach ~10 Tbps.</div>
